<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Dark spot on my CRT. Any suggestions?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10520&amp;p=118541#p118541"><![CDATA[
Could be a flaw in the aperture grille / mesh.<br />Could be a speck of dust or carbon (impurity) that blocked one of the holes in the mesh.<br />Could be a dead area in the phosphor layer.<br /><br />I would say one of these is most likely.  My gaming monitor has a microscopic dark spot on the screen too.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Sun Sep 22, 2013 7:07 pm</p><hr />
